  p PostShot Privacy Policy

  p This Privacy Policy describes how PostShot collects, uses, and discloses your personal information when you use our Service.

  p By using our Service, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this policy. This policy is a legally binding agreement between you and us.

  h2 Information We Collect

  p We collect information that you provide directly to us when you use our Service, such as your name, email address, and any other information you choose to provide.

  h2 Use of Information

  p We use the information we collect to provide and improve our Service. We may use your information to communicate with you about or respond to your requests for information.

  h2 Disclosure of Information

  p We may disclose your personal information in the following situations:

  ul
    li When we believe it is necessary to comply with law, governmental requests, or a judicial or regulatory order, such as in response to a court order or subpoena.
    li When we need to enforce or apply our Terms of Service, including investigation of potential violations.
    li When we otherwise need to provide you with updated or differentiated information in response to changes to our Service or other changes that affect you.
    li When we need to contact you to notify you of an update to our Service that requires or requires you to opt-in to new uses of your personal information.

  h2 Security of Your Information

  p We take reasonable measures to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, use, or disclosure. However, no method of transmission over the Internet, or method of electronic storage, is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee its absolute security.

  h2 Children's Privacy

  p Our Service does not address anyone under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personally identifiable information from children under 13. If you are a parent or guardian and you are aware that your child has provided us with personal information, please contact us at info@postshot.app.

  h2 Changes to This Privacy Policy

  p We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page.

  p We will let you know via email and/or a prominent notice on our Service, prior to the change becoming effective and update the "Last updated" date at the top of this Privacy Policy.

  h2 Contact Us

  p If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at info@postshot.app.
